ally lonely), and I noticed lots of new stuff.<br>
<br>
Aside from Clentun leaving the game (something I dealt with in its own thread), I also saw Lohengrin's profile (which he updated!).  It included some new lewtz, of course, but I was pretty amazed to see some of his stats over 255.  I guess that means they raised those old caps, lol, although who knows if the returns are marginally diminished, or better yet, who cares!<br>
<br>
You know, for the first time in a long time, I was able to get on the site, look around... and suddenly feel a bit better about not being around.  I mean, I still miss the people (and the lewtz of course), but I'm coping much better than I used to.  All said, I am not going the leave the site miserable and depressed.  Instead, I'll just be happy to be breaking the cycle, and happy for all those who still are able to find enjoyment in it.  I dunno how Verant's done over the 8ish months since the great bard has disappeared, but I can only assume it's much of the same.<br>
<br>
So, keep up the good work, but you don't need me to tell you that to do it regardless, eh?<br>
<br>
By the way, board trolling really is as pathetic as it seems.<br>
<br>
Oh yes, and all that stuff I said a bit ago about breaking the cycle will be COMPLETELY null and void when World of Warcraft debuts and my life, as it has been known, comes to its end, and the saga of the greatest Orc Warchief ever is born.<br>
<br>
Sigh, so sad.<br>
<br>
Excelsior!!<br>
Melvyn / Adrian<br>
